README
 Created on: 26.7.2015
     Author: Alvar
     
     Data transmission (TCP)
     	Important: it is vital that functions using the connectionTimer variable are not called inside the TIM7_Irq, which
     	increments the counter.
     	
     	Lat and long are transferres as microdegrees.
     	
     	message is sent in 
     	Message style: #D,1,2,3,4,5,6#D1,2,3,4,5,6#D1,2,3,4,5,6*c#R
     
     
     EEPROM data organiztion: 
     	
     	floating point values = [-321.68, 327.67]: 2 bytes/parameter. Example: kpRoll = 12.34, floatArray[0] = kpRoll*100=1234.
     	Addresses 0-255 -> 128 parameters max. Must be written in blocks of 32 parameters max.
     	Parameter = user-defined value
     	
     	Current parameters:
     	
	 	kpRoll 			floatArray[0]
		kpPitch 		floatArray[1]
		kpYaw 			floatArray[2]
		kpCrs 			floatArray[3]
		kpAs 			floatArray[4]
		kpThrPitch 		floatArray[5]
		kpFp 			floatArray[6]
		kpVertSpd 		floatArray[7]
		
		kiRoll 			floatArray[8]
		kiPitch 		floatArray[9]
		kiYaw 			floatArray[10]
		kiCrsRud 		floatArray[11]
		kiFp 			floatArray[12]
		kiAs 			floatArray[13]
		
		kdRoll 			floatArray[14]
		kdPitch 		floatArray[15]
		dYaw 			floatArray[16]
		kdCrs 			floatArray[17]
		kdFp 			floatArray[18]
		kdAs 			floatArray[19]
		
		lpfGainFp 		floatArray[20]
		lpfGainErrFp 	floatArray[21]
		lpfGainCrs 		floatArray[22]
		lpfGainGpsCrs 	floatArray[23]
		
		
		maxVertSpd 		floatArray[24]
		minVertSpd 		floatArray[25]
		maxAs 			floatArray[26]
		minAs 			floatArray[27]
		minAsClb 		floatArray[28]
		minAsRoll 		floatArray[29]
		crzAs 			floatArray[30]
		maxBankAbs 		floatArray[31]
		maxBankNav 		floatArray[32]
		maxPitch 		floatArray[33]
		minPitch 		floatArray[34]
		maxVertSpdTurn 	floatArray[35]
		
		
		Integer values = [-32768, 32768]: 2 bytes/value. For example the last ADC offset, Accelerometer offsets etc.
     	Addresses 256-383 -> 64 values max. Must be written in blocks of 32 values max.
     	Calibration = dependant of the current state of the system
     	
     	Current calibration values and similar:
     	
     	Cruize altitude:
     	crzAlt			intArray[0]
     	
     	Servo output values:
     	iMaxAil 		intArray[1]
		iMaxEle 		intArray[2]
		iMaxThr 		intArray[3]
		iMaxCrsRud 		intArray[4]
		iMaxFp 			intArray[5]    
		
		maxThr 			intArray[6]
		minThr 			intArray[7]
		maxAilThrow 	intArray[8]
		maxEleThrow 	intArray[9]
		maxRudThrow 	intArray[10]
     	
     	Acc & gyro offsets:
     	offset.ax		intArray[11]
     	offset.ay		intArray[12]
     	offset.az		intArray[13]
     	offset.gx		intArray[14]
     	offset.gy		intArray[15]
     	offset.gz		intArray[16]
     	
     	Control end-points:
		minAilOut		intArray[17]
		maxAilOut		intArray[18]
		minEleOut		intArray[19]
		maxEleOut		intArray[20]
		minRudOut		intArray[21]
		maxRudOut		intArray[22]
		
		TCP connection checksum:
		TCPChecksum	intArray[23]
		
		ADC offset:
		adcU0			intArray[24]
		
		Altimeter offset:
		h0    			intArray[25]
     	
     	Waypoints: lat + lon = float+float = 8 bytes per waypoint. Altitude is a constant cruize altitude value.
     	Addresses 384-639 -> 32 waypoints max. Must be written in blocks of 8 parameters max.
     	
     	Flight data etc: In blocks of size of 1, 2 or 4 bytes.
     	Addresses 640->32767

     	-The page layout of 64 bytes affects the above numbers(It has been taken into account though).
     	-The EEPROM_ReadBuffer size is 512 bytes atm.